              | Quantity Surveying
            p Experience world-class teaching and develop practical expertise in areas such as building technology, finance, economics and law. During this flexible, project-focused degree you will use our Building Information Modelling laboratory to develop excellent employability skills, have the option to work with industry professionals on real construction projects, and have the option for UK study.  
            p Accredited by the Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors (RICS), the Chartered Institute of Building (CIOB) and with (provisional) accreditation from the Board of Quantity Surveyors Malaysia (BQSM), this course is a great basis for careers in quantity surveying, as well as other construction roles such as project management, construction management and cost consultancy. 
